    L05_P1_p1: "Have you ever heard of the \"Ig Nobel Prizes\"? Last month, I read several online news articles about them and found the articles very amusing.",
    L05_P1_p2: "The Ig Nobel Prizes were started by Marc Abrahams, the American editor of a humorous magazine about science, in 1991. The prizes are awarded annually for the ten greatest achievements that first make people laugh, and then think. The following are three examples of prize-winning research. 1. Do potato chips taste better if they sound crunchier? (Nutrition Prize, 2008)",
    L05_P1_p3: "Italian and British researchers worked together to find out whether potato chips that sound better taste better. In their experiment, they asked volunteers to eat potato chips while wearing headphones. When the crunching sounds were made louder in the headphones, the chips were rated crisper and fresher than they really were.",
    L05_P1_full: "Have you ever heard of the \"Ig Nobel Prizes\"? Last month, I read several online news articles about them and found the articles very amusing. The Ig Nobel Prizes were started by Marc Abrahams, the American editor of a humorous magazine about science, in 1991. The prizes are awarded annually for the ten greatest achievements that first make people laugh, and then think. The following are three examples of prize-winning research. 1. Do potato chips taste better if they sound crunchier? (Nutrition Prize, 2008) Italian and British researchers worked together to find out whether potato chips that sound better taste better. In their experiment, they asked volunteers to eat potato chips while wearing headphones. When the crunching sounds were made louder in the headphones, the chips were rated crisper and fresher than they really were.",

    L05_P2_p1: "One Japanese research group invented the wasabi-based alarm system. It gives off wasabi gas in case of a fire. At the very first stage of the research, the researchers had been thinking of how to wake up people with hearing disabilities in an emergency. They had tried hundreds of odors, including rotten eggs, before deciding on wasabi. An ingredient in wasabi stimulates nerves in the nose, and even people sleeping deeply cannot help waking up.",
    L05_P2_p2: "3. What can we do for mice to live longer? (Medicine Prize, 2013) A group including Japanese researchers found that a particular kind of music helped mice with heart transplants live longer. Mice normally stayed alive for an average of seven days after the operation. However, those listening to Mozart lived for 20 days, and those listening to Italian opera survived for 27 days. Do you think music will also help you live longer?",
    L05_P2_full: "One Japanese research group invented the wasabi-based alarm system. It gives off wasabi gas in case of a fire. At the very first stage of the research, the researchers had been thinking of how to wake up people with hearing disabilities in an emergency. They had tried hundreds of odors, including rotten eggs, before deciding on wasabi. An ingredient in wasabi stimulates nerves in the nose, and even people sleeping deeply cannot help waking up. 3. What can we do for mice to live longer? (Medicine Prize, 2013) A group including Japanese researchers found that a particular kind of music helped mice with heart transplants live longer. Mice normally stayed alive for an average of seven days after the operation. However, those listening to Mozart lived for 20 days, and those listening to Italian opera survived for 27 days. Do you think music will also help you live longer?",

    L05_P3_p1: "Well, what do you think about those research findings? Have you become interested in the Ig Nobel Prizes? According to Marc Abrahams, there are 9,000 new nominations for the Ig Nobel Prizes every year, so it is very difficult to win a prize. The only criterion for a prize-winning achievement is based on whether or not people laugh at first, and then a week later still want to tell their friends about it.",
    L05_P3_p2: "To my surprise, the winners are not given any prize money. Instead, they are given a handmade award. In addition, they have to pay their own transportation costs to attend the Ig Nobel ceremony at Harvard University. At the ceremony, the prizes are handed out by genuine Nobel Prize winners. Wow!",
    L05_P3_p3: "You can learn a lot more about amusing achievements from the Ig Nobel Prizes website. Why don't you check it out, get a big laugh, and then THINK?!",
    L05_P3_full: "Well, what do you think about those research findings? Have you become interested in the Ig Nobel Prizes? According to Marc Abrahams, there are 9,000 new nominations for the Ig Nobel Prizes every year, so it is very difficult to win a prize. The only criterion for a prize-winning achievement is based on whether or not people laugh at first, and then a week later still want to tell their friends about it. To my surprise, the winners are not given any prize money. Instead, they are given a handmade award. In addition, they have to pay their own transportation costs to attend the Ig Nobel ceremony at Harvard University. At the ceremony, the prizes are handed out by genuine Nobel Prize winners. Wow! You can learn a lot more about amusing achievements from the Ig Nobel Prizes website. Why don't you check it out, get a big laugh, and then THINK?!",

